      "comment" : "Weak layers in the old snowpack can be released even easily by individual winter sport participants. Caution is to be exercised in particular on steep west, north and east facing slopes above the tree line. Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground and reach large size in isolated cases. <br/> The fresh and somewhat older wind slabs can be released easily or naturally. The avalanche prone locations are sometimes covered with new snow and are barely recognisable because of the poor visibility."
